103
00:06:22,000 --> 00:06:23,300
Oh, no, it's not that.

104
00:06:24,090 --> 00:06:25,090
Hmm?

105
00:06:25,390 --> 00:06:26,590
I think...

106
00:06:26,630 --> 00:06:29,040
I've just had a shocking realization.

107
00:06:29,880 --> 00:06:31,410
Or rather, um...

108
00:06:34,430 --> 00:06:35,430
We...

109
00:06:36,790 --> 00:06:38,430
might not be dating.

110
00:06:41,520 --> 00:06:42,760
We're not dating?

111
00:06:45,290 --> 00:06:47,660
He definitely told me he likes me.

112
00:06:48,170 --> 00:06:49,170
And I said it back.

113
00:06:49,650 --> 00:06:51,080
But now that I think about it,

114
00:06:51,240 --> 00:06:55,790
we've never actually talked about
whether or not we're dating.

115
00:06:56,710 --> 00:06:58,840
Should I ask him about it?

116
00:06:59,710 --> 00:07:02,710
'Are we dating?'

117
00:07:03,150 --> 00:07:04,350
No, no way.

118
00:07:04,350 --> 00:07:05,890
There's no way I could ask that.

119
00:07:06,340 --> 00:07:07,340
Hioki...

120
00:07:07,410 --> 00:07:08,810
Huh? Oh, yes!

121
00:07:09,030 --> 00:07:10,230
Do you have a minute?

122
00:07:10,920 --> 00:07:12,410
I'd like to talk to you alone.

123
00:07:13,160 --> 00:07:14,160
Huh?

124
00:07:14,550 --> 00:07:15,550
Oh.

125
00:07:15,700 --> 00:07:16,700
Oh, okay.

126
00:07:27,850 --> 00:07:28,850
Your hands must be cold.

127
00:07:29,370 --> 00:07:30,370
Oh.

128
00:07:30,540 --> 00:07:31,540
A little.

129
00:07:31,790 --> 00:07:33,100
Here, take this.

130
00:07:33,480 --> 00:07:34,480
Oh.

131
00:07:34,630 --> 00:07:35,630
Th...

132
00:07:41,590 --> 00:07:43,060
What should I do?

133
00:07:43,630 --> 00:07:45,000
Maybe I really should ask.

134
00:07:45,480 --> 00:07:46,480
But...

135
00:07:46,710 --> 00:07:48,360
Oh, um...

136
00:07:50,180 --> 00:07:51,180
Yeah?

137
00:07:52,630 --> 00:07:53,630
Oh, it's nothing.

138
00:07:53,740 --> 00:07:54,740
Um...

139
00:07:56,670 --> 00:07:58,430
Oh, speaking of which, this place...

140
00:07:58,650 --> 00:08:00,070
We came here on our way back
from the school trip, didn't we?

141
00:08:00,730 --> 00:08:01,730
Oh.

142
00:08:02,600 --> 00:08:03,600
Yeah.

143
00:08:05,900 --> 00:08:06,460
Speaking of that,

144
00:08:06,460 --> 00:08:08,510
didn't we draw fortunes that day?

145
00:08:09,630 --> 00:08:10,630
Yeah.

146
00:08:10,730 --> 00:08:11,930
My fortune,

147
00:08:12,260 --> 00:08:13,980
do you remember what it said?

148
00:08:14,970 --> 00:08:16,070
Hmm, what was it?

149
00:08:17,860 --> 00:08:20,270
'Believe in yourself and move forward.'

150
00:08:20,920 --> 00:08:21,920
What's that about?

151
00:08:22,790 --> 00:08:24,130
It was actually pretty spot-on.

152
00:08:24,580 --> 00:08:25,790
- Right?
- Yeah.

153
00:08:26,630 --> 00:08:28,950
In fact, it's because I tried
to move forward after that

154
00:08:29,593 --> 00:08:31,350
that I get to be here with you like this now.

155
00:08:31,860 --> 00:08:34,650
Yeah, the gods really knew
what they were talking about.

156
00:08:37,400 --> 00:08:38,400
But,

157
00:08:39,390 --> 00:08:41,670
that part actually worries me a little.

158
00:08:42,590 --> 00:08:43,590
Huh?

159
00:08:44,930 --> 00:08:46,130
I might...

160
00:08:47,840 --> 00:08:49,820
just keep rushing forward on my own.

161
00:08:51,230 --> 00:08:52,430
And because I'm too hasty,

162
00:08:53,710 --> 00:08:56,210
I might end up causing you trouble.

163
00:08:57,460 --> 00:08:58,460
So,

164
00:08:59,720 --> 00:09:00,720
if

165
00:09:01,310 --> 00:09:02,940
I start to get out of control,

166
00:09:04,610 --> 00:09:05,610
you have to stop me.

167
00:09:07,040 --> 00:09:08,040
Out of control...

168
00:09:11,690 --> 00:09:12,890
I want

169
00:09:14,090 --> 00:09:15,420
to cherish you properly.

170
00:09:28,240 --> 00:09:29,420
Oh, right.

171
00:09:29,820 --> 00:09:31,810
I have something for you. Sit down for a sec.

172
00:09:32,390 --> 00:09:33,390
Huh?

173
00:09:33,560 --> 00:09:34,560
Okay.

174
00:09:40,900 --> 00:09:42,430
Close your eyes first.

175
00:09:43,430 --> 00:09:44,430
Okay.

176
00:09:50,970 --> 00:09:51,970
You can open them now.

177
00:09:54,370 --> 00:09:55,370
Huh?

178
00:09:56,190 --> 00:09:57,560
Merry Christmas.

179
00:09:59,410 --> 00:10:00,510
Thank you.

180
00:10:00,910 --> 00:10:01,910
Go on, open it.

181
00:10:01,990 --> 00:10:03,760
Ooh, I wonder what it is.

182
00:10:16,760 --> 00:10:17,760
A watch...

183
00:10:18,770 --> 00:10:19,770
Yeah.

184
00:10:20,290 --> 00:10:22,500
